<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Yoshi Studio - Social Media Assignment - Navya Verma</title>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Cormorant+Garamond:ital,wght@0,300;0,400;0,500;1,300;1,400&family=DM+Sans:wght@300;400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
  :root {
    --cream: #F5F0E8;
    --warm-white: #FAF7F2;
    --ink: #1A1714;
    --terracotta: #C4622D;
    --gold: #B8942A;
    --dusty-rose: #D4A5A0;
    --sage: #8A9B7E;
    --muted: #7A7168;
    --border: #E0D8CC;
  }

  * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }

  body {
    background: var(--warm-white);
    color: var(--ink);
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  /* COVER */
  .cover {
    min-height: 100vh;
    background: var(--ink);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: flex-start;
    padding: 80px 100px;
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .cover::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: -100px; right: -100px;
    width: 500px; height: 500px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(184,148,42,0.12) 0%, transparent 70%);
  }

  .cover::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    bottom: -80px; left: 200px;
    width: 400px; height: 400px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(196,98,45,0.1) 0%, transparent 70%);
  }

  .cover-tag {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 3px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gold);
    margin-bottom: 40px;
  }

  .cover h1 {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: clamp(52px, 7vw, 88px);
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 1.05;
    color: var(--cream);
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .cover h1 em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--gold);
  }

  .cover-sub {
    font-size: 15px;
    color: rgba(245,240,232,0.5);
    margin-top: 28px;
    letter-spacing: 0.5px;
  }

  .cover-meta {
    position: absolute;
    bottom: 80px;
    right: 100px;
    text-align: right;
    font-size: 12px;
    color: rgba(245,240,232,0.35);
    letter-spacing: 1px;
  }

  .divider-line {
    width: 40px;
    height: 1px;
    background: var(--gold);
    margin: 32px 0;
  }

  /* SECTIONS */
  section {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 100px 60px;
  }

  section.full-bleed {
    max-width: 100%;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .section-label {
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 4px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--terracotta);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  h2 {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: clamp(32px, 4vw, 48px);
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin-bottom: 40px;
    color: var(--ink);
  }

  h2 em { font-style: italic; color: var(--terracotta); }

  h3 {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 22px;
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.3px;
  }

  p {
    font-size: 15px;
    color: #3D3830;
    line-height: 1.85;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  /* BRAND BRIEF BOX */
  .brand-brief {
    background: var(--ink);
    color: var(--cream);
    padding: 56px 64px;
    margin: 60px 0;
    position: relative;
  }

  .brand-brief::before {
    content: '"';
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 200px;
    color: rgba(184,148,42,0.08);
    position: absolute;
    top: -20px; left: 30px;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .brand-brief .brand-name {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 36px;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--gold);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .brand-brief p {
    color: rgba(245,240,232,0.75);
    font-size: 14px;
    max-width: 600px;
  }

  .brand-brief .brand-essence {
    margin-top: 24px;
    padding-top: 24px;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
    font-size: 13px;
    color: rgba(245,240,232,0.45);
    letter-spacing: 0.5px;
  }

  /* PILLARS */
  .pillars-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 2px;
    margin: 40px 0;
  }

  .pillar {
    background: var(--cream);
    padding: 36px 32px;
    border-left: 3px solid transparent;
    transition: border-color 0.3s;
  }

  .pillar:nth-child(1) { border-left-color: var(--terracotta); }
  .pillar:nth-child(2) { border-left-color: var(--gold); }
  .pillar:nth-child(3) { border-left-color: var(--sage); }
  .pillar:nth-child(4) { border-left-color: var(--dusty-rose); }

  .pillar-emoji { font-size: 22px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .pillar h3 { font-size: 18px; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .pillar p { font-size: 13.5px; margin-bottom: 0; color: var(--muted); }

  /* CADENCE */
  .cadence-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 2px;
    margin: 40px 0;
  }

  .cadence-item {
    background: var(--cream);
    padding: 32px 28px;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .cadence-num {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 52px;
    font-weight: 300;
    color: var(--terracotta);
    line-height: 1;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .cadence-label {
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  /* TREND BOX */
  .trend-box {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 40px 44px;
    margin: 40px 0;
    position: relative;
  }

  .trend-box::before {
    content: 'TREND TO TAP';
    position: absolute;
    top: -8px; left: 40px;
    background: var(--warm-white);
    padding: 0 12px;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 3px;
    color: var(--gold);
  }

  /* CALENDAR */
  .calendar-section {
    background: var(--cream);
    padding: 80px 60px;
  }

  .calendar-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 2px;
    margin-top: 48px;
  }

  .cal-day {
    background: var(--warm-white);
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 80px 1fr 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 0;
    min-height: 100px;
  }

  .cal-day-num {
    background: var(--ink);
    color: var(--cream);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    padding: 20px 10px;
  }

  .cal-day-num .day-name {
    font-size: 9px;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: rgba(245,240,232,0.4);
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }

  .cal-day-num .day-number {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 32px;
    font-weight: 300;
    color: var(--cream);
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .cal-day:nth-child(2) .cal-day-num,
  .cal-day:nth-child(4) .cal-day-num,
  .cal-day:nth-child(6) .cal-day-num {
    background: var(--terracotta);
  }

  .cal-cell {
    padding: 20px 24px;
    border-left: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .cal-cell-label {
    font-size: 9px;
    letter-spacing: 2.5px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }

  .cal-cell p {
    font-size: 13px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .format-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 3px 10px;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 1.5px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    border-radius: 2px;
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }

  .badge-reel { background: rgba(196,98,45,0.12); color: var(--terracotta); }
  .badge-carousel { background: rgba(184,148,42,0.12); color: var(--gold); }
  .badge-story { background: rgba(138,155,126,0.15); color: var(--sage); }
  .badge-static { background: rgba(212,165,160,0.2); color: #9A6B66; }

  /* CAPTION SECTION */
  .caption-section {
    background: var(--ink);
    padding: 80px 60px;
  }

  .caption-section .section-label { color: var(--gold); }
  .caption-section h2 { color: var(--cream); }

  .caption-post-ref {
    display: inline-block;
    background: rgba(245,240,232,0.08);
    padding: 8px 18px;
    font-size: 12px;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
    color: rgba(245,240,232,0.5);
    margin-bottom: 40px;
  }

  .caption-body {
    background: rgba(245,240,232,0.05);
    border-left: 2px solid var(--gold);
    padding: 40px 48px;
    max-width: 640px;
  }

  .caption-body p {
    color: rgba(245,240,232,0.85);
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 2;
    white-space: pre-line;
  }

  .caption-tags {
    margin-top: 28px;
    padding-top: 24px;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(245,240,232,0.1);
    font-size: 13px;
    color: rgba(245,240,232,0.35);
    line-height: 2;
  }

  .caption-note {
    margin-top: 40px;
    max-width: 540px;
  }

  .caption-note h3 {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gold);
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .caption-note p {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: rgba(245,240,232,0.5);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  /* PERFORMANCE */
  .perf-section {
    padding: 100px 60px;
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .diagnosis-steps {
    margin: 40px 0;
    counter-reset: steps;
  }

  .step {
    display: flex;
    gap: 28px;
    margin-bottom: 32px;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .step-num {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 36px;
    height: 36px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--terracotta);
    color: white;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-top: 3px;
  }

  .step-content h3 {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 15px;
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
    letter-spacing: 0;
    color: var(--ink);
  }

  .step-content p { font-size: 14px; margin-bottom: 0; color: var(--muted); }

  .action-box {
    background: var(--cream);
    border-top: 3px solid var(--terracotta);
    padding: 40px 44px;
    margin-top: 48px;
  }

  .action-box h3 {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 24px;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .action-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .action-list li {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: #3D3830;
    padding: 10px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    display: flex;
    gap: 12px;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .action-list li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

  .action-list li::before {
    content: '→';
    color: var(--terracotta);
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-top: 1px;
  }

  /* CLOSING */
  .closing {
    background: var(--ink);
    padding: 80px 100px;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: flex-end;
  }

  .closing-left h2 {
    color: var(--cream);
    font-size: 40px;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .closing-left p {
    color: rgba(245,240,232,0.4);
    font-size: 13px;
  }

  .closing-right {
    text-align: right;
    font-size: 12px;
    color: rgba(245,240,232,0.25);
    letter-spacing: 1px;
  }

  hr.section-break {
    border: none;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    margin: 0 60px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 700px) {
    .cover { padding: 60px 36px; }
    section { padding: 60px 28px; }
    .pillars-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .cadence-row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .cal-day { grid-template-columns: 60px 1fr; grid-template-rows: auto auto auto; }
    .closing { flex-direction: column; gap: 32px; padding: 60px 36px; }
    .brand-brief { padding: 36px 28px; }
    .caption-section { padding: 60px 28px; }
    .calendar-section { padding: 60px 28px; }
    .perf-section { padding: 60px 28px; }
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<!-- COVER -->
<div class="cover">
  <div class="cover-tag">Yoshi Studio - Social Media Manager Assignment - Navya Verma</div>
  <h1>The Quiet<br>Festival<em>.</em></h1>
  <div class="divider-line"></div>
  <p style="color:rgba(245,240,232,0.55); font-size:15px; max-width:460px; line-height:1.8;">
    A 4-week Instagram strategy for a minimalist Indian homewear brand launching its first festive collection, where restraint becomes ceremony.
  </p>
  <div class="cover-meta">
    Navya Verma <br>
	Brand Archetype A<br>
    Minimalist Indian Homewear
  </div>
</div>


<!-- BRAND BRIEF -->
<section>
  <div class="section-label">Starting Point</div>
  <h2>The Brand I'm Working With</h2>
  <p>Before building a strategy, I always build a brand picture that grounds every content decision.</p>

  <div class="brand-brief">
    <div class="brand-name">Ghar.</div>
    <p>A minimalist Indian homewear label rooted in slow living. Natural fabrics, muted palettes, craft-forward production. Their aesthetic sits at the intersection of Indian heritage and contemporary restraint - block-print meets Brutalism.</p>
    <p style="margin-top:12px">Their audience: urban, design-literate Indian millennials who find Diwali decor overwhelming and are looking for a version of the festive season that feels like them.</p>
    <div class="brand-essence">
      Brand Voice: Calm. Intentional. Warm without being loud. &nbsp;|&nbsp; Tone: Like a letter from a friend with good taste.
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>Everything below is built for this brand. The strategic principles, however, apply to any minimalist homewear brand in this space.</p>
</section>

<hr class="section-break">


<!-- STRATEGY SNAPSHOT -->
<section>
  <div class="section-label">Section 01 — Strategy</div>
  <h2>Instagram Strategy<br><em>Snapshot</em></h2>
  <p>Four weeks. One launch. The approach isn't to flood feeds, but to build the kind of quiet anticipation that makes people feel like they discovered something.</p>

  <div style="margin: 40px 0 28px">
    <h3 style="font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif; font-size:13px; letter-spacing:2px; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--muted); margin-bottom:20px;">Content Pillars</h3>
  </div>

  <div class="pillars-grid">
    <div class="pillar">
      <div class="pillar-emoji">🪔</div>
      <h3>The Collection</h3>
      <p>Product-led content that shows how pieces live in real spaces. Never just product shots, always context. Mood over catalogue.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="pillar">
      <div class="pillar-emoji">🧵</div>
      <h3>The Craft</h3>
      <p>Behind-the-material storytelling. Where the fabric comes from, how it's made, what makes it different from fast-homewear. Builds trust before purchase.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="pillar">
      <div class="pillar-emoji">🏠</div>
      <h3>The Ritual</h3>
      <p>How people actually use this stuff. Setting a table. Morning chai. An evening with candles lit. Sells the life, not the product.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="pillar">
      <div class="pillar-emoji">💬</div>
      <h3>The Conversation</h3>
      <p>Community touchpoints - prompts, polls, responses. "How do you celebrate quietly?" This pillar builds belonging, not just following.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div style="margin: 56px 0 24px">
    <h3 style="font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif; font-size:13px; letter-spacing:2px; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--muted); margin-bottom:20px;">Posting Cadence</h3>
  </div>

  <div class="cadence-row">
    <div class="cadence-item">
      <div class="cadence-num">5×</div>
      <div class="cadence-label">Posts per week</div>
      <p style="font-size:12px; color:var(--muted); margin-top:10px; margin-bottom:0;">Consistent enough to build habit. Sparse enough to feel intentional.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="cadence-item">
      <div class="cadence-num">3–4×</div>
      <div class="cadence-label">Stories per day</div>
      <p style="font-size:12px; color:var(--muted); margin-top:10px; margin-bottom:0;">Stories carry the personality: behind-the-scenes, polls, quick moments.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="cadence-item">
      <div class="cadence-num">2×</div>
      <div class="cadence-label">Reels per week</div>
      <p style="font-size:12px; color:var(--muted); margin-top:10px; margin-bottom:0;">Used for reach, not for clout. Quiet, cinematic, no jump cuts.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div style="margin: 56px 0 24px">
    <h3 style="font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif; font-size:13px; letter-spacing:2px; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--muted); margin-bottom:4px;">Format Mix</h3>
  </div>

  <p>
    <strong>Carousels (40%)</strong> — Great for storytelling, saves, and reach. Used for craft narratives, collection reveals, and "how to style" content.<br><br>
    <strong>Reels (30%)</strong> — Drives reach. Shot like short films: slow zooms, natural light, ambient sound. Never trending audio that doesn't fit the brand.<br><br>
    <strong>Static + Stories (30%)</strong> — Single images for mood-setting. Stories for conversation, polls, and humanising the brand.
  </p>

  <div class="trend-box">
    <h3 style="margin-bottom:12px;">Trend: "Slow Festive" Content</h3>
    <p style="margin-bottom:12px;">There's a growing counter-reaction on Instagram to the maximalist Diwali content that saturates feeds every October - too much glitter, too many transitions, too loud. Creators and small brands are finding real traction with a quieter aesthetic: single-take videos, natural light, no music or very understated ambient sound.</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom:0; color:var(--muted); font-size:14px;">
      <strong>Why it works for this brand:</strong> It's not a trend they're chasing, but one that's catching up to them. Their minimalist DNA is already aligned. A single Reel of a diya being lit next to a linen table runner, shot in golden hour, no voiceover, will feel deeply intentional while also tapping into a format that's performing.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div style="background:var(--cream); padding:28px 32px; margin-top:16px; border-left: 3px solid var(--sage);">
    <h3 style="font-family:'DM Sans'; font-size:13px; letter-spacing:1px; text-transform:uppercase; font-weight:500; margin-bottom:8px;">4-Week Arc</h3>
    <p style="font-size:13.5px; margin-bottom:6px; color:var(--ink)"><strong>Week 1:</strong> Tease - mood content, "something is coming", craft story.</p>
    <p style="font-size:13.5px; margin-bottom:6px; color:var(--ink)"><strong>Week 2:</strong> Reveal - collection launch, hero pieces, shopping-linked content.</p>
    <p style="font-size:13.5px; margin-bottom:6px; color:var(--ink)"><strong>Week 3:</strong> Deepen - styling, ritual content, UGC encouragement.</p>
    <p style="font-size:13.5px; margin-bottom:0; color:var(--ink)"><strong>Week 4:</strong> Close - last-chance messaging, community moments, post-festive warmth.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<hr class="section-break">


<!-- CONTENT CALENDAR -->
<div class="calendar-section">
  <div style="max-width:900px; margin:0 auto;">
    <div class="section-label">Section 02 — Content</div>
    <h2>6-Day Content<br><em>Calendar</em></h2>
    <p style="max-width:580px;">Set in Week 2, the launch week. The collection has just been revealed; now we layer in story, desire, and conversation.</p>

    <div class="calendar-grid">

      <!-- Day 1 -->
      <div class="cal-day">
        <div class="cal-day-num">
          <div class="day-name">MON</div>
          <div class="day-number">01</div>
        </div>
        <div class="cal-cell">
          <div class="cal-cell-label">Format</div>
          <span class="format-badge badge-reel">Reel</span>
          <p>60-sec launch film</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cal-cell">
          <div class="cal-cell-label">Visual Concept</div>
          <p>Single-take golden-hour walkthrough of a styled room. Diya lit. Linen curtain moving slightly. No voiceover, only ambient sound and a single low note of music at the end.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cal-cell">
          <div class="cal-cell-label">Caption Direction</div>
          <p>Minimal. Two lines: "The festive season, the way you want it." + "Shop the Utsav Collection - link in bio." Let the video do the talking.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Day 2 -->
      <div class="cal-day">
        <div class="cal-day-num">
          <div class="day-name">TUE</div>
          <div class="day-number">02</div>
        </div>
        <div class="cal-cell">
          <div class="cal-cell-label">Format</div>
          <span class="format-badge badge-carousel">Carousel</span>
          <p>6-slide product story</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cal-cell">
          <div class="cal-cell-label">Visual Concept</div>
          <p>Each slide = one hero piece. Flat lay on textured stone or natural wood. Tight crops. Slide 6 shows all pieces together in a room, the full picture after parts.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cal-cell">
          <div class="cal-cell-label">Caption Direction</div>
          <p>Name the collection pieces with one sentence each on what inspired them. End with: "Swipe through the Utsav Collection." Educate, don't sell.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Day 3 -->
      <div class="cal-day">
        <div class="cal-day-num">
          <div class="day-name">WED</div>
          <div class="day-number">03</div>
        </div>
        <div class="cal-cell">
